            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Average Temperatures: Daytime highs 75-90°F, overnight lows 50-65°F, decreasing daily temperature ranges\n\nHeat Pump Performance: October remains primarily a cooling month with occasional heating needed during cool mornings. November transitions to more balanced heating/cooling with mild days requiring neither mode and cool nights needing heat. Heat pumps excel during these swing seasons, automatically switching modes without homeowner intervention when thermostats are in 'auto' mode.\n\nOptimization Tips: Take advantage of mild fall weather opening windows for free cooling during pleasant 70-75°F days and running heat pumps only during temperature extremes. Schedule fall professional tune-up in October-November preparing heating system for winter operation. Clean or replace filters before heating season begins ensuring adequate airflow. Test emergency heat function to verify backup heat works before potential cold weather needs arise. Adjust thermostat schedules accounting for shorter daylight hours and earlier temperature drops.\n\nEnergy Costs: Expect $100-$170/month with mixed operation, enjoying some of the lowest HVAC costs of the year during Tucson's pleasant fall weather."
