            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Typical Heat Pump Repair Costs in Tucson\n\nReversing Valve Replacement: $450-$850 – Controls heat/cool mode switching; failure means stuck in one mode\n\nDefrost Control Board: $300-$550 – Manages defrost cycles; failure causes ice buildup or constant defrosting\n\nCapacitor Replacement: $150-$300 – Common failure; causes compressor or fan motor not to start\n\nContactor Replacement: $125-$275 – Electrical relay; clicking sounds often indicate failure\n\nRefrigerant Leak Repair: $400-$1,200+ – Cost depends on leak location; includes leak repair and refrigerant recharge\n\nCompressor Replacement: $1,800-$3,500 – Most expensive repair; often triggers replacement vs repair decision\n\nAir Handler Blower Motor: $450-$850 – Indoor unit motor failure; causes no airflow\n\nThermostat Replacement: $150-$450 – Smart thermostats at higher end; basic models less expensive\n\nCondensate Drain Clearing: $125-$250 – Prevents water damage from backed-up condensate"
