            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Properly maintained heat pumps last 15-20 years—comparable to traditional air conditioners and gas furnaces. The key difference is heat pumps operate year-round rather than seasonally, meaning they require more frequent filter changes and benefit from bi-annual maintenance (spring and fall) rather than annual tune-ups. With regular professional maintenance, quality brands like Carrier, Trane, and Lennox routinely exceed 20-year lifespans in Tucson's mild climate. The lack of combustion components (no burners, heat exchangers, or gas valves to corrode) often gives heat pumps longevity advantages over furnaces."
